        <!-- Project Overview -->
        <div class="project-section">
            <h3>Project Overview</h3>
            <p>
                This project demonstrates how to set up and manage a <strong>PostgreSQL database</strong> on AWS RDS and use Alembic for incremental schema migrations:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Database Setup</strong> – Launched a PostgreSQL database instance on AWS RDS using AWS CLI.</li>
                <li><strong>Alembic Integration</strong> – Configured Alembic with SQLAlchemy and psycopg2 to connect Python to PostgreSQL.</li>
                <li><strong>Migrations</strong> – Created and applied migration scripts to add and manage database tables.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The goal was to implement reliable, version-controlled schema changes in a cloud-hosted database.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Architecture -->
        <div class="project-section alt-bg">
            <h3>Architecture Explanation</h3>
            <p>The architecture includes the following components:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>AWS RDS (PostgreSQL)</strong> – Cloud-hosted database instance.</li>
                <li><strong>SQLAlchemy</strong> – Python ORM for defining schema objects.</li>
                <li><strong>Alembic</strong> – Migration tool for version-controlling schema changes.</li>
                <li><strong>psycopg2</strong> – Python driver enabling communication with PostgreSQL.</li>
                <li><strong>psql Client</strong> – Used to verify and manually inspect tables created in RDS.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Key Learnings -->
        <div class="project-section">
            <h3>Key Learnings</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Learned how to launch and configure an AWS RDS PostgreSQL database using AWS CLI.</li>
                <li>Understood how Alembic tracks migrations like Git commits for databases.</li>
                <li>Created and applied multiple migration scripts (e.g., <code>account</code>, <code>account2</code> tables).</li>
                <li>Verified migrations using the PostgreSQL <code>psql</code> client.</li>
                <li>Gained experience in integrating Python tools with cloud databases.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Notes & Best Practices -->
        <div class="project-section alt-bg">
            <h3>Notes & Best Practices</h3>
            <p>
                While this project focused on demonstrating migrations in a learning environment, in production:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Credentials should be managed securely (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager).</li>
                <li>Security groups should restrict PostgreSQL access to trusted IPs, not open to the world.</li>
                <li>Separate environments (dev, staging, prod) should each maintain their own migration history.</li>
                <li>Monitoring and backups should be enabled for RDS databases to ensure reliability.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

